window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>She doesn’t believe in monsters—until one becomes her boss.</p> <p>Claire Benolt doesn’t do supernatural. Ghosts, vampires, werewolves? Total nonsense. Or so she thought.</p> <p>Eager to outrun her troubled past, Claire jumps at the chance to work for a private investigator in New Orleans. But her new boss isn’t exactly your average detective—he’s a centuries-old vampire with a taste for justice, and he needs Claire’s help to stop a brutal serial killer known only as the Ripper.</p> <p>Then there’s Mason—a dangerously charming Nightwalker with a wicked smile and an appetite that has nothing to do with blood. He’s got his sights set on Claire, and resisting him might be more dangerous than giving in.</p> <p>With a killer on the loose and creatures of the night closing in, Claire must confront a world she never believed in... or become the next victim.</p>"; 
